result.execSummary:
The defendant Justin Deangelo Hollis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property >$2500-$5000, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: *Pay restitution in the amount of $3,000 to victim, Home Depot, FIRST.  There is to be a wage assignment done to start paying restitution.

*Pay supervision fees.
*Provide a DNA sample - pay surcharge.
*Pay all remaining mandatory costs, fees, surcharges and assessments by the end of probation period or balance to convert to civil judgment.

*Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess any gun or other firearms. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.
*Advise any and all potential employers of conviction.
